<h3 dir="auto" class="">Future Food Tech: Beyond Plant-BasedвАФBreaking It Down</h3>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This ainвАЩt your grandmaвАЩs tofu slab; this is food tech so ballsy itвАЩd make a butcher weep into his apron.</p>
<ol dir="auto" class="marker:text-secondary">
<li class="break-words"><strong>Centrifugal Filtration + Variegated Compression Freezing/Frying</strong><br>
Picture this: Spinning vats of plant mushвАФthink pea protein, hemp oil, whateverвАФwhipped into submission by centrifugal force, separating the good shit from the chaff. Then we hit it with variegated compressionвАФfreezing some layers to lock in that juicy snap, frying others for a crispy, golden edge. ItвАЩs like building a steak from the molecule up: marbled fat, tender chew, crispy searвАФall without a cowвАЩs sad moo in sight. WeвАЩre talking physics as the chef, crafting textures so real youвАЩd swear it bled, but itвАЩs just goddamn lentils playing dress-up.</li>
<li class="break-words"><strong>Modified Yogurts &amp; Fermented Bases</strong><br>
Fungal proteins, algae, bioengineered microbesвАФthese little bastards are the MVPs. WeвАЩre fermenting them into creamy, funky bases you can tweak on the fly. Want a brie that melts like sin? Dial up the yeast. Craving bacon fat that sizzles and pops? Crank the fungal funk. These arenвАЩt static recipesвАФtheyвАЩre living, breathing substrates, tunable like a goddamn synthesizer. Labs are already doing this with dairyвАФletвАЩs push it into overdrive, churning out everything from silky cheeses to smoky lard, all from a vat of slime thatвАЩd make a vegan high-five a scientist.</li>
<li class="break-words"><strong>3D-Printed Avocado вАЬMeatвАЭ</strong><br>
