<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Centrifugal vats hum in the ruins, spinning plant scraps into marbled miraclesвАФlayers of fat and fiber compressed into bites that crackle and melt, mocking the memory of meat. Fermentation labs glow in the dark, fungal kings and algal gods churning out bases that shift with a flick of a dial: brie one day, bacon the next, all from the same slime that once fed fish. And in the heart of it, 3D printers sing, layering avocado вАЬmeatвАЭ into slabs of creamy defianceвАФcheap, clean, and born from the ashes of a world that drowned in its own excess.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">This isnвАЩt survival; itвАЩs supremacy. No more kneeling to natureвАЩs whims or the slaughterhouseвАЩs blade. We build our feasts from the ground upвАФphysics, microbes, and machines as our cooks. The old guard mocked us, called it weak, na√ѓve. But their barbecues are graves now, and our tables groan with bounty theyвАЩll never taste. The revolutionвАЩs here, and itвАЩs delicious.</p>
