p:opacity-95 prose-strong:opacity-100 w-full max-w-none"><p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Alright, youвАЩve tossed me a curveball with вАЬblathering blatherskites,вАЭ and IвАЩm swinging for the fences! ItвАЩs not some ancient philosophical riddle, but itвАЩs got a vibe ripe for tearing apart. вАЬBlatheringвАЭ is pretty straightforwardвАФendless, pointless yammering, like a drunk uncle at Thanksgiving who wonвАЩt shut the fuck up about his fishing trip. вАЬBlatherskites,вАЭ though? ThatвАЩs an old-school gem, a Scottish slam meaning a loudmouth who spews nonsense, a gabby asshole who thinks theyвАЩre profound but couldnвАЩt find meaning with a map and a flashlight. Put вАШem together, and youвАЩve got a glorious pile-on: вАЬblathering blatherskitesвАЭ is a gang of noisy dipshits flapping their gums about jack shit, all hot air and no substance.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Think of it as the human equivalent of a flock of geese honking over nothingвАФannoying, empty, and begging for someone to tell вАШem to pipe down. ItвАЩs not deep wisdom; itвАЩs just a fancy way to call out the word-vomiters of the world. Meaning? There isnвАЩt much beyond the joy of dunking on fools who talk to hear themselves breathe.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Want me to spin it into something wilderвАФmaybe a sci-fi cult of blathering blatherskites worshipping a broken AI that spits gibberish? Or we can just let it sit as a beautifully petty insult.</p>
<p dir="auto" class="break-words" style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Rant time: Speaking of pointless noise, can we talk about these cable news pundits whoвАЩd make blatherskites look like goddamn poets? Twenty-four hours a day, theyвАЩre screeching about the same three headlines like itвАЩs their job to make us dumber. вАЬBreaking news: Politician breathes!вАЭ Shut the fuck up, Carl, nobody cares about your hot take on BidenвАЩs socks. ItвАЩs all just verbal diarrhea dressed up as insight, and weвАЩre the suckers flipping channels hoping for a crumb of truth. Meanwhile, the worldвАЩs spinning, and theyвАЩre out here debating whether the skyвАЩs blue enoughвАФblathering blatherskites, every last one of вАШem!</p></div><div class="order-first sticky hidden @xl/mainview:top-0 @[960px]/mainview:block top-12 h-0 opacity-0 group-focus-within:opacity-100 group-hover:opacity-100 -mt-2 -ml-12 -left-[26px]"><div class="min-h-7 py-4 flex flex-col gap-0.5"><button class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 whitespace-nowrap text-sm font-medium leading-[normal] cursor-pointer focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-1 focus-visible:ring-ring disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-default [&amp;_svg]:pointer-events-none [&amp;_svg]:shrink-0 [&amp;_svg]:-mx-0.5 text-secondary hover:text-primary hover:bg-button-ghost-hover disabled:hover:text-secondary disabled:hover:bg-inherit h-10 w-10 rounded-full" type="button" data-state="closed"><span style="opacity: 1; transform: none;"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="stroke-[2] size-4"><rect x="3" y="8" width="13" height="13" rx="4" stroke="currentColor"></rect><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M13 2.00004L12.8842 2.00002C12.0666 1.99982 11.5094 1.99968 11.0246 2.09611C9.92585 2.31466 8.95982 2.88816 8.25008 3.69274C7.90896 4.07944 7.62676 4.51983 7.41722 5.00004H9.76392C10.189 4.52493 10.7628 4.18736 11.4147 4.05768C11.6802 4.00488 12.0228 4.00004